<item>
            <title>[CXF-2724] Relative schema location import fails on Windows machines</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2724</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I have a WSDL that imports a schema from a relation path such as below, it does not work in Windows.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;		&amp;lt;xsd:schema xmlns:xsd=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;			&amp;lt;xsd:&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; namespace=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;urn:RelPath&quot;&lt;/span&gt; schemaLocation=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;../schemas/configuration/bar.xsd&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
			&amp;lt;/xsd:&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
		&amp;lt;/xsd:schema&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is because of two issues in org.apache.cxf.resource.URIResolver.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) URIResolver checks for baseUriStr.startsWith(&quot;file:/&quot;) but Windows file URI could be &quot;file:C:/foo/bar&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) URIResolver would include fragment (e.g. #type2) as file path when creates a File object.  This is not showing up as a problem in UNIX machines because &quot;new URI(baseUriStr)&quot; is able to parse the baseUriStr correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
